00:10:42.030 --> 00:10:45.810
in your smartphone, LinkedIn
contacts, who you just haven't

00:10:45.810 --> 00:10:47.310
talked to in maybe years.

00:10:47.310 --> 00:10:50.220
And reconnecting with
people, now it's not sleazy.

00:10:50.220 --> 00:10:50.940
It's not scary.

00:10:50.940 --> 00:10:52.110
You already know
these people, you're

00:10:52.110 --> 00:10:53.193
already friends with them.

00:10:53.193 --> 00:10:55.620
So reconnecting with people
is a really great way

00:10:55.620 --> 00:10:57.900
to increase your network size.

00:10:57.900 --> 00:11:00.450
And you don't have to have any
awkwardness or any sleaziness

00:11:00.450 --> 00:11:02.550
because they're people
you already know.

00:11:02.550 --> 00:11:07.100
A second thing that's
pretty simple is when--

00:11:07.100 --> 00:11:09.900
I think this was
research by Brian Uzzi

00:11:09.900 --> 00:11:13.360
and Sharon Dunlap-- was that
there are super connectors.

00:11:13.360 --> 00:11:15.636
If you look through
your contact list,

00:11:15.636 --> 00:11:17.760
you're going to find that
a disproportionate number

00:11:17.760 --> 00:11:20.440
of people were introduced to
you by a handful of people.

00:11:20.440 --> 00:11:22.740
We all have that one
friend who introduced us

00:11:22.740 --> 00:11:24.420
to so many other friends.

00:11:24.420 --> 00:11:26.400
Those people are your
super connectors.

00:11:26.400 --> 00:11:28.544
So if you want to
build your network,

00:11:28.544 --> 00:11:30.210
and you only have
limited time, you only

00:11:30.210 --> 00:11:31.751
have limited resources,
then you want

00:11:31.751 --> 00:11:33.420
to give a
disproportionate attention

00:11:33.420 --> 00:11:34.800
to those super connectors.

00:11:34.800 --> 00:11:37.991
And ask them, hey, I'm looking
for a new job, who should I

00:11:37.991 --> 00:11:38.490
talk to?

00:11:38.490 --> 00:11:40.080
Hey, I'm looking
to make new friends

00:11:40.080 --> 00:11:41.160
in a new city I move to.

00:11:41.160 --> 00:11:42.450
Who should I talk to?

00:11:42.450 --> 00:11:45.870
Those super connectors
are the hubs of networks.

00:11:45.870 --> 00:11:47.910
And that's where
you're going to get

00:11:47.910 --> 00:11:49.077
the most bang for your buck.

