like what you say

00:13:21.390 --> 00:13:24.090
to yourself is going
to magically create

00:13:24.090 --> 00:13:25.840
money, or success, or whatever.

00:13:25.840 --> 00:13:29.230
But, in terms of the
things you say to yourself,

00:13:29.230 --> 00:13:31.560
the Navy, basically
after 9/11, the Navy

00:13:31.560 --> 00:13:34.110
wanted to increase the
number of Navy SEALs.

00:13:34.110 --> 00:13:39.200
But if you reduce the threshold
for the difficulty of BUD/S,

00:13:39.200 --> 00:13:42.780
the vetting program, then the
SEALs aren't going to be good.

00:13:42.780 --> 00:13:44.280
So they were
thinking, how can we

00:13:44.280 --> 00:13:47.740
help people get through it
without lowering standards?

00:13:47.740 --> 00:13:50.820
And one of the four
things that they realized

00:13:50.820 --> 00:13:52.971
was positive self-talk.

00:13:52.971 --> 00:13:54.720
Because that story
you're telling yourself

00:13:54.720 --> 00:13:57.060
in your head becomes a
self-fulfilling prophecy.

00:13:57.060 --> 00:13:59.750
And there's tons of
research, much of it

00:13:59.750 --> 00:14:03.240
done by Martin Seligman, in
terms of the power of optimism.

00:14:03.240 --> 00:14:05.970
Where just when we
believe we can, it makes

00:14:05.970 --> 00:14:07.810
sense to continue.

00:14:07.810 --> 00:14:09.090
It's pretty intuitive.

00:14:09.090 --> 00:14:12.510
When you feel like things
aren't going to work out,

00:14:12.510 --> 00:14:13.770
why would you persist?

00:14:13.770 --> 00:14:15.930
When you think things are
going to work out then

00:14:15.930 --> 00:14:17.010
it makes sense.

00:14:17.010 --> 00:14:18.750
So when your
self-talk is positive,

00:14:18.750 --> 00:14:23.040
when you see positive things
in your life as personal,

00:14:23.040 --> 00:14:25.139
you're responsible for
them, they're permanent,

00:14:25.139 --> 00:14:26.430
they're going to keep on going.

00:14:26.430 --> 00:14:27.240
And that they are
pervasive-- they're

00:14:27.240 --> 00:14:28.750
affecting a big
area of your life.

00:14:28.750 --> 00:14:30.000
You're more likely to persist.

00:14:30.000 --> 00:14:31.440
You're more likely to go on.

00:14:31.440 --> 00:14:33.270
And that was one
of the key things

00:14:33.270 --> 00:14:35.670
that helped recruits get
through Navy SEAL training.

00:14:35.670 --> 00:14:36.930
