00:17:47.090 --> 00:17:49.194
You talked about the ghost army.

00:17:49.194 --> 00:17:51.360
Can you go into that and
how it plays into the book?

00:17:51.360 --> 00:17:51.660
ERIC BARKER: Yeah.

00:17:51.660 --> 00:17:53.220
Basically, in
World War II, there

00:17:53.220 --> 00:17:57.420
was a whole unit that was
dedicated toward deception.

00:17:57.420 --> 00:17:59.370
Where, basically,
their goal was--

00:17:59.370 --> 00:18:04.750
you're talking about less than
1,000 men whose job it was to--

00:18:04.750 --> 00:18:08.590
these were artists and
guys who might not have fit

00:18:08.590 --> 00:18:10.330
in other areas of the military.

00:18:10.330 --> 00:18:13.450
And their job was to be less
than 1,000 men who appeared

00:18:13.450 --> 00:18:16.450
to be 10,000 or more soldiers.

00:18:16.450 --> 00:18:18.340
So they could
actually fill in gaps

00:18:18.340 --> 00:18:20.170
in the line in World War II.

00:18:20.170 --> 00:18:23.860
And there was a unit that had
huge speakers that would play

00:18:23.860 --> 00:18:25.870
the sounds of tanks coming.

00:18:25.870 --> 00:18:29.230
They had 95-pound
inflatable tanks,

00:18:29.230 --> 00:18:31.090
which occasionally
they'd use a rope

00:18:31.090 --> 00:18:35.140
to keep the barrel of the tank
up because it would deflate.

00:18:35.140 --> 00:18:38.770
But from the sky, enemy
planes, recon planes

00:18:38.770 --> 00:18:41.860
would see what looks like
tanks from a quarter mile away.

00:18:41.860 --> 00:18:43.510
They'd hear the sound of tanks.

00:18:43.510 --> 00:18:45.550
And they even had
radio operators

00:18:45.550 --> 00:18:49.450
who would be making fake
signals to sound like there

00:18:49.450 --> 00:18:51.160
was a huge division there.

00:18:51.160 --> 00:18:54.310
And I talk about
this in the context

00:18:54.310 --> 00:18:58.990
of when we are presenting
ourselves to others--

00:18:58.990 --> 00:19:02.200
is it good to try and deceive?

00:19:02.200 --> 00:19:04.000
This was effective
in World War II.

00:19:04.000 --> 00:19:08.320
But deceiving others
as to who you are

00:19:08.320 --> 00:19:10.210
can be an effective
short-term strategy,

00:19:10.210 --> 00:19:13.090
but it's usually not a very
effective long-term strategy.

00:19:13.090 --> 00:19:14.886
SPEAKER 1: Especially if people
