00:19:14.886 --> 00:19:15.510
not the real deal.

00:19:15.510 --> 00:19:17.593
ERIC BARKER: Eventually,
you develop a reputation.

00:19:17.593 --> 00:19:21.050
Eventually, people
do see who you are.

00:19:21.050 --> 00:19:23.627
And in terms of the
issue of ethics--

00:19:23.627 --> 00:19:25.210
so in the book, when
I talk about when

00:19:25.210 --> 00:19:27.370
nice guys finish last.

00:19:27.370 --> 00:19:31.750
That whole idea-- often
it's split into the issue

00:19:31.750 --> 00:19:33.880
of short term versus long term.

00:19:33.880 --> 00:19:37.329
And a lot of
negative, bad traits

00:19:37.329 --> 00:19:38.870
are very effective
in the short term,

00:19:38.870 --> 00:19:41.510
but they're not effective
in the long term.

00:19:41.510 --> 00:19:44.230
So if you look at
narcissists, narcissists

00:19:44.230 --> 00:19:47.890
do better in job interviews,
they do better on first dates.

00:19:47.890 --> 00:19:51.820
But what you see is after
a few weeks on the job,

00:19:51.820 --> 00:19:53.890
