work inside of an organization.

00:25:36.290 --> 00:25:40.970
And it depends on what are
your skills, if your skills are

00:25:40.970 --> 00:25:42.300
drawing people together.

00:25:42.300 --> 00:25:45.260
We're seeing increasingly people
are able to work on their own.

00:25:45.260 --> 00:25:47.180
They're able to do
their own thing.

00:25:47.180 --> 00:25:49.760
But most people are going
to work for organizations.

00:25:49.760 --> 00:25:52.790
And so I don't think
that's the only way.

00:25:52.790 --> 00:25:55.280
SPEAKER 1: Gotcha.

00:25:55.280 --> 00:25:59.420
Can talk about Tim
Kreider's stabaversary.

00:25:59.420 --> 00:26:01.612
ERIC BARKER: Yeah.

00:26:01.612 --> 00:26:04.520
Tim Kreider, a
cartoonist, and when

00:26:04.520 --> 00:26:07.100
he was on vacation in Greece
he was actually stabbed

00:26:07.100 --> 00:26:09.720
in the neck and almost died.

00:26:09.720 --> 00:26:12.860
He described it as there's
a difference of about one

00:26:12.860 --> 00:26:16.460
millimeter between him
going home in coach

00:26:16.460 --> 00:26:19.640
and him going home
in the cargo hold.

00:26:19.640 --> 00:26:24.200
And the thing was, when he
came home, for the next year,

00:26:24.200 --> 00:26:29.000
he was basically incapable
of being sad or disappointed

00:26:29.000 --> 00:26:32.300
because he was just so
thrilled to be alive.

00:26:32.300 --> 00:26:34.280
He was so happy
because everything was

00:26:34.280 --> 00:26:37.160
compared to I could be dead.

00:26:37.160 --> 00:26:40.370
But after a year, things
started to frustrate him again.

00:26:40.370 --> 00:26:42.619
He started to get sad again.

00:26:42.619 --> 00:26:43.910
You can't sustain that forever.

00:26:43.910 --> 00:26:46.550
So he started celebrating
his stabaversary,

00:26:46.550 --> 00:26:50.660
the day when he got stabbed,
to kind of remind him, hey, I'm

00:26:50.660 --> 00:26:52.040
lucky to be here.

00:26:52.040 --> 00:26:54.499
