00:38:04.644 --> 00:38:06.310
ERIC BARKER: The issue
of overconfidence

00:38:06.310 --> 00:38:07.101
is really critical.

00:38:09.560 --> 00:38:12.370
I think Malcolm Gladwell
talked about this in a lecture

00:38:12.370 --> 00:38:14.380
he gave.

00:38:14.380 --> 00:38:18.100
Underconfidence is the
sins of the amateur.

00:38:18.100 --> 00:38:20.240
Overconfidence is the
sin of the expert.

00:38:20.240 --> 00:38:22.870
So the real danger comes
from overconfidence,

00:38:22.870 --> 00:38:27.190
because we trust experts
